ilt environments, but rather made and remade worlds for the living and the dead. Wang explores the multifaceted and multifunctional diagrammatic tradition of rendering space in early China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCartographyzChinaxHistory. 0aCartographyzChinaxMethodologyxHistory. 0aEarly mapszChinaxHistory. 0aTombszChina. 7aTechnology & Engineering / General.2bisacsh  aChina, ditu, diagram, map, worldmaking, topology, Zhongshan, Mawangdui, Fangmatan.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131912408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023z9783111318165oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226827476423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226827476/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131912-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEIb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023